Edoardo Saccaro [@saccaedo] challenges isolation and total silence in a truly extreme landscape.

New Zealand is a guarantee for the winter lovers: when in the western empisphere is summer, over there you can keep on losing yourself between the endless massive glaciers that slide into the ocean.
@pietro_lamaro and his fellow travellers @adventure.addicted spent 7 days surrounded by a breathtaking environment.
Read the story of the adventure on the link in bio.

Days are quite long and temperatures stable in Norway during spring; the snow conditions remain untouched by the sun. In a place like this, surrounded by peaks and couloirs, only one can be the explanation: one has twelve hours to have fun skiing.

Women’s bodies have a shape and structure that differ from those of men and our Randonnée backpack has been designed specifically to match women’s anatomy. A versatile 30-liter winter mountaineering and ski mountaineering backpack designed to keep your back and shoulders dry thanks to the breathability of the Contact Flow system and to the micro-ventilation integrated in the back.

Thanks to all of you who have chosen to join us to promote change: all sales from the #GreenFriday event allowed us to make a donation to two environmental associations we believe in: EOCA, Plastic Mountain to Sea Project for Europe and POW, @protectourwinters in the US.

Today is our #GreenFriday: this year, once again, our aim is for it to become an opportunity to do some concrete activity for the environment. This is why, in addition to the 20% discount on all your online and offline purchases, we’ll be donating 3% of total proceeds to a sustainable project. 
Find out more on the link in bio.

We believe in sustainability and environmental protection. We are committed to maintaining a long-term perspective in what we do. This is why we’ve decided, for the second year now, to support an association in favour of the environment: 3% of proceeds during #GreenFriday will be donated to a sustainable project. Find out more on the link in bio.

Huge congrats to him and to the overall winner for the @redbullillume Image Quest 2019: @benthouard.

Extreme skiing is a subtle compromise between thrill and concentration, maximum attention mixed with fun. Each movement is controlled, but the emotions felt are unrivalled.
@pietro_lamaro knows it very well as he just skied the Col du Plan, one of the most iconic lines. 
Read his full story on the link in bio.

We asked our athletes the same questions and each of them told us something new about themselves and about their relationships with the mountains. As a result, we discovered that @francoiscazzanelli is very careful regarding the equipment he uses; he always brings the minimum with him (but you’ll always find Nutella in his backpack). Travelling to Lofoten Islands, Norway, is like going back in time. Same feeling of when the Italian Alps emerged from the sea: sharp peaks, steep couloirs and ridges emergining from the sea, lit by the Midnight Sun.
Elia Lazzari experienced a new type of mountain adventure, in these lands, where time stands still. Read the story on link in bio.

Preparations are in full swing for the award ceremony in Plan de Corones; in a few days we’ll know who are the winners of the @redbullillume Image Quest 2019, the largest adventure and action sports photography competition in the world. 
Credit: Nic Alegre | Photographer / @tetongravity

When he was 16 @jacek_matuszek found his home in the vertical walls and the Dolomites became his second home. Lately he also started paragliding making a dream come true: “you reach the top and wish you could fly down... you can really do it!”
.

Skiing on fresh snow is the best feeling in the world: you feel at one with nature, drawing zigzag lines behind you.
Instead of being cozy in our hotel room or at home, wrapped in a blanket, we chose to travel to the Russian far east of Kamchatka, with winds blowing at 100 km/hour and a devastating cold, looking for the perfect line.
Read the full story on the link in bio.

Skier: @arnaudcottet

We have grown so accustomed to noise, we don’t even notice anymore. We accept it as a constant in our lives. But when we are up there, we learn to appreciate silence, talk less, and let Nature be the background of our thoughts, with its distant sounds.
The mountain says nothing, yet speaks to your heart. 
Read the full story on the link in bio.

Credit: @simone.mondino

@arnaudcottet: from freestyle races to pure passion for skitouring.
Arnaud spent his life between travelling and skiing new peaks. He spaced from extreme skiing in Alaska to Afghanistan’s breath-taking mountains. He made the most of New Zealand and visited the classic Dolomites.
A fun fact? When he’s not on the slopes, he is a teacher.
